import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['u'], data['v'])
    plt.xlabel('u')
    plt.ylabel('v')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the range of values for 'u' and 'v' coordinates?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    top_10_percent = data.nlargest(int(len(data) * 0.1), ['u', 'v'])
    plt.scatter(top_10_percent['u'], top_10_percent['v'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title("What is the relationship between 'u' and 'v' coordinates for the top 10% of data points?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
